cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the matching of music audio snippets to the corresponding pixel location in images of sheet music, which involves image processing and pattern recognition. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with audio processing and matching it to sheet music, which falls under the domain of sound. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may involve the use of social networks or information networks to gather data or information related to sheet music and audio snippets. 
4. cs.SD (Software Development) - The paper may involve the development of software or tools for sheet music processing and audio matching. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the processing of both image and audio data, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
